cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.DS, cs.NE 

The paper deals with clustering of unstructured textual data, which is a common problem in information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of n-grams and immune systems for clustering also involves natural language processing (cs.CL) and data structures (cs.DS). Additionally, the use of biomimetic approaches falls under the category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
